[assistant] Fixed the failing test by avoiding nested interfaces.
[assistant] 
[assistant] The failure came from loading `ProxyMockMakerInnerCommonClassLoaderTest$LeftInterface` through a child class loader while the enclosing test class was loaded by the parent, which caused the JVM `InnerClasses` attribute mismatch during Mockito’s mock-name derivation.
[assistant] 
[assistant] Changes made:
[assistant] 
[assistant] - Updated `ProxyMockMakerInnerCommonClassLoaderTest.java`
[assistant]   - Replaced nested-interface binary names with top-level interface names.
[assistant]   - Removed nested `LeftInterface` / `RightInterface`.
[assistant] 
[assistant] - Added support interfaces:
[assistant]   - `ProxyMockMakerCommonLeftInterface.java`
[assistant]   - `ProxyMockMakerCommonRightInterface.java`
[assistant] 
[assistant] These top-level interfaces can be isolated by the custom class loaders without triggering `InnerClasses` metadata validation issues, while preserving the intended coverage path through `ProxyMockMaker.CommonClassLoader.loadClass(...)`.
[assistant-event] text_end
